faviconNotify
-------------

A small library to display a red notification bubble in your favourate icon.
Done in JavaScript and Canvas, so should work in a drop-in fashion.
Works atleast on Chrome and Firefox.


Usage:

  FaviconNotify.set(string);
  FaviconNotify.clear();


Example:

  <html>
    <head>
      <link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico">
      <script src="faviconNotify.js"></script>
      <script>
        window.onblur = function() {
          FaviconNotify.set(1);
        };
        window.onfocus = function() {
          FaviconNotify.clear();
        };
      </script>
    </head>
  </html>
